724816f-a.text:
Wooster Street, south from Grand Street to its southern end at Canal Street. Wooster Street is the third of a group of seven streets
laid out parallel to and west of Broadway.
The building in the background is the new New York Telephone Building.
June 23, 1933.
L. Sperr.
